theorem P3_iInter_of_P3_closed_finite
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Type*} [Finite ι] {S : ι → Set X}
    (hClosed : ∀ i, IsClosed (S i))
    (hP3 : ∀ i, Topology.P3 (S i)) :
    Topology.P3 (⋂ i, S i) := by
  classical
  -- Each `S i` is open because it is both closed and satisfies `P3`.
  have hOpen : ∀ i, IsOpen (S i) := by
    intro i
    exact (Topology.open_of_P3_closed (A := S i) (hClosed i)) (hP3 i)
  -- A finite intersection of open sets is open.
  have hOpenInter : IsOpen (⋂ i, S i : Set X) := by
    simpa using isOpen_iInter (fun i => hOpen i)
  -- Any open set satisfies `P3`.
  exact Topology.open_satisfies_P3 (A := ⋂ i, S i) hOpenInter

theorem nonempty_of_nonempty_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (interior (A : Set X)).Nonempty → A.Nonempty := by
  rintro ⟨x, hxInt⟩
  exact ⟨x, (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A) hxInt⟩
